1 (267) Wildlife Resources. – Issuable to the registered owner of a motor vehicle in
2 accordance with G.S. 20-81.12. The plate shall bear the phrase "Wildlife
3 Resources Commission" with a picture in the background representing a
4 native wildlife species occurring in North Carolina.
5 …."
6 SECTION 2.(c) G.S. 20-81.12 reads as rewritten:
7 "§ 20-81.12. Collegiate insignia plates and certain other special plates.
8 …
9 () Lifetime Conservationist. – The Division must transfer quarterly the money in the
10 Collegiate and Cultural Attraction Account derived from the sale of Lifetime Conservationist
11 plates to the Wildlife Resources Fund established in G.S. 143-250.
12 …
13 (b163) Wildlife Resources Plates. Resources. – The Division must receive 300 or more
14 applications for a wildlife resources plate with a picture representing a particular native wildlife
15 species occurring in North Carolina before the plate may be developed. The Division must
16 transfer quarterly the money in the Collegiate and Cultural Attraction Plate Account derived from
17 the sale of wildlife resources plates to the Wildlife Conservation Account established by
18 G.S. 143-247.2.
19 …."
